##What is a Personal Brand

Literally speaking, it is your blog/personal website, social media, product pages, emails and other other online presence.
More generally, it is what people think of when they hear your name or your business' name, ie its reputation.

<span class="caps">C</span>reating a personal blog is all the rage, and has been since the [mid 2000s](http://www.webdesignerdepot.com/2011/03/a-brief-history-of-blogging/).
Blogging/personal websites and social media curation are integral to managing an online identify.

Despite a seemingly saturated market, more blogging and social media sites are continually rising up and settling into their respective niches.
In this article we'll cover how to decide if you need an online brand and how to navigate the application landscape to get started.

